Save-and-exit on SIGHUP/SIGTERM for the Brogue CE curses build (late.sh door
hosting; applied by the Dockerfile brogue-build stage, re-verify on CE bumps).

Upstream only auto-saves an interrupted game in the SDL platform (window-close
calls quitImmediately); the curses build dies unsaved on a hangup, so an SSH
disconnect or a host rollout would lose the run. This installs a hangup handler
that runs the same quitImmediately save path (flush the recording, write the
suspend .broguesave) and exits. quitImmediately is prompt- and UI-free, so it
is safe enough to run from a terminating signal handler; the dgamelaunch
NetHack servers have relied on the same save-on-SIGHUP shape for decades.

--- a/src/platform/curses-platform.c
+++ b/src/platform/curses-platform.c
@@ -2,12 +2,25 @@
 #include <string.h>
 #include <stdint.h>
 #include <signal.h>
+#include <unistd.h>
 #include <sys/time.h>
 #include "platform.h"
 #include "term.h"

+// late.sh: on hangup (SSH disconnect) or SIGTERM (host shutdown), save the
+// game in progress exactly like the SDL platform's window-close path, so the
+// run resumes next launch instead of being lost. quitImmediately never
+// prompts or draws; _exit skips curses teardown (the terminal is gone).
+static void handleHangup(int sig) {
+    (void)sig;
+    quitImmediately();
+    _exit(EXIT_STATUS_SUCCESS);
+}
+
 static void gameLoop() {
     signal(SIGINT, SIG_DFL); // keep SDL from overriding the default ^C handler when it's linked
+    signal(SIGHUP, handleHangup);
+    signal(SIGTERM, handleHangup);

     if (!Term.start()) {
         return;
